nti-thyroid peroxidase antibodies","Anti-thyroglobulin antibodies","Anti-thyroid stimulating hormone receptor antibodies","Anti-thyroxine antibodies","Anti-triiodothyronine antibodies"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnti-thyroid peroxidase (anti-TPO) antibodies\u003C/strong\u003E are the most sensitive serological marker for Hashimoto thyroiditis, being present in approximately 95% of cases. While \u003Cstrong\u003Eanti-thyroglobulin antibodies\u003C/strong\u003E are also commonly found, they are only present in about 60% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnti-thyroid stimulating hormone receptor antibodies\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristically associated with Graves disease rather than Hashimoto thyroiditis. \u003Cstrong\u003EAnti-thyroxine antibodies\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eanti-triiodothyronine antibodies\u003C/strong\u003E are not typically associated with autoimmune thyroid disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of anti-TPO antibodies, together with typical clinical and ultrasound findings, helps establish the diagnosis of Hashimoto thyroiditis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Anti-thyroid peroxidase (anti-TPO) antibodies are present in approximately 95% of Hashimoto thyroiditis cases","Anti-thyroglobulin antibodies are found in about 60% of Hashimoto thyroiditis cases","Anti-TPO antibodies are the most sensitive diagnostic marker for Hashimoto thyroiditis"],"references":["Klubo-Gwiezdzinska J, Wartofsky L. Hashimoto thyroiditis: an evidence-based guide to etiology, diagnosis and treatment. Pol Arch Intern Med. 2022 Mar 30;132(3):16222. doi: 10.20452/pamw.16222. Epub 2022 Mar 3. PMID: 35243857; PMCID: PMC9478900","Caturegli P, De Remigis A, Chuang K, Dembele M, Iwama A, Iwama S. Hashimoto\u0027s thyroiditis: celebrating the centennial through the lens of the Johns Hopkins hospital surgical pathology records. Thyroid. 2013 Feb;23(2):142-50. doi: 10.1089/thy.2012.0554. PMID: 23151083; PMCID: PMC3569966","Patil N, Rehman A, Anastasopoulou C, et al. Hypothyroidism. [Updated 2024 Feb 18]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519536/","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55845"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15589"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55845","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55845"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T20:13:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T20:16:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8280"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70381"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"